KCB Bank Group Foundation are leading the path, by collaborating with Clean Start Kenya to get PROXIMATE to girls and women, impacted by the justice system. By putting pen to paper and signing this MoU, we are committing to change the NARRATIVES for this community that has deliberately been UNHEARD, UNSEEN and UNDERFUNDED and DARING to go beyond the ordinary by offering them mentorship programs under KCB's secondary, tertiary and university scholarships, access to opportunities in TVET's, and Enterprise Development training.
    KCB Foundation will also identify and facilitate internship or industrial attachment opportunities for the beneficiaries during and after their studies to propel the gaining of hands-on experience, which is an indispensable part of vocational training.
